parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dual clutch transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or stall, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the "Transmission Overheating" message is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch assembly can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or stall, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the "Transmission Overheating" message is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Oil pump failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine replacement.
Timing belt failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine replacement.
Turbocharger failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine replacement.
Fuel system issues can cause stalling, difficulty starting, and uneven engine performance.
Clutch and transmission issues can cause difficulty shifting, stalling, and loss of power.
The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose motive power, and hesitate while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle stalls or hesitates while accelerating
the vehicle jerks or shakes while driving
the vehicle fails to start immediately after refueling
and the vehicle has a rough idle.
